        "fix": "add an expression before the operator",
        "hint": "Binary operators like +, -, *, =, etc. require both a left and right operand.\n\nFor example:\n  ```ocaml\n  let x = 1 + 2   (* correct *)\n  let y = 1 +     (* missing right operand *)\n  let z = + 2     (* missing left operand *)\n  ```\n\nIf you want to create a partially applied operator function, use parentheses:\n  ```ocaml\n  let add_one = (+) 1\n  ```\n"
      },
